name: V Kohli
commentary: tiki-taka catch between Rahane and Ravindra at midwicket. Looks like a slightly slower ball, which is why Kohli has not got all on this pull, and Rahane takes the diving catch at deep midwicket and lobs it to Ravindra before sliding into the boundary cushions

name: F du Plessis
commentary: The Fizz strikes in his first over this IPL. The cutter from Mustafizur. Bowls at 130ks, on a length, outside off, du Plessis early into it, and ends up miscuing it to deep point

name: RM Patidar
commentary: double strike for the Fizz. He has been done in by pace again. A Test-match dismissal. On a good length, wobble-seam, just going with the angle. No feet from Patidar, slightly late on it, edges it through

name: GJ Maxwell
commentary: CSK have come roaring back. Maxwell is gone for a golden duck. What a huge wicket. Short of a length, top of off or thereabouts, Maxwell looks to punch at it with an open face. The face is just too open. Edges it to Dhoni. Actually off the face of the bat. This game has turned on its head

name: C Green
commentary: four for Fizz. Hits the top of leg. The cutter from Mustafizur. Short of a length, pitches outside leg, Green makes room to look to crash it into the covers. Beaten by the turn

name: Anuj Rawat
commentary: wide yorker again, DK has shuffled across so it won't be called. Rawat tries to steal a bye, and Dhoni catches him short with a direct hit. "You still got it"

name: RD Gaikwad
commentary: Edged and taken on the second attempt by Green at first slip. This is excellent bowling and also excellent captaincy from Faf to keep the slip in. Keeps it on a length but well outside off stump. Gaikwad gets forward reaching for the drive. He gets a thick edge and Green takes a fairly simple catch albeit on the second attempt. Important wicket for RCB

name: R Ravindra
commentary: He's gone now! One shot too many for Rachin. Was a length ball on middle and leg. He sweeps eyeing another six, but doesn't connect as cleanly. Deep backward square leg settles himself and takes a comfortable catch. Lovely debut for Rachin who falls for a 15-ball 37.

name: AM Rahane
commentary: Excellent catch by Maxwell at square leg and Rahane's sprightly knock ends. Back of a length ball but the line was crucial here. It was outside off, which meant Rahane had to fetch it and he could not control his pull. Maxwell is a few steps in from the boundary. But he adjusts well, and takes a reverse-cupped catch over his head

name: DJ Mitchell
commentary: The short ball does the trick for Green! Banged in short outside off, Mitchell was looking to go over long-on. Does not get any power on the pull and Patidar makes no mistake at long-on.

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: DA Warner
commentary: lovely slower bouncer. Harshal is celebrating a catch at the wicket, but the umpire hasn't given it. PBKS review it. Ultra Edge confirms there is a bit of a tope edge and also a chunk of the glove on the ball. Warner has to go

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: MR Marsh
commentary: wide on the crease, wide half-volley, Marsh square-drives, but finds short cover-point to perfection. Arshdeep has got lucky with this one

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: SD Hope
commentary: Rabada comes back. This length ball, bowled at 141ks, might have just stopped a touch on him and Hope almost plays a check-drive straight and low to short cover

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: RR Pant
commentary: Patel makes up for the drop catch. And again with the slower short ball. Bowled at 123ks, Pant looks to ramp it behind square, but the lack of pace means he ends up lobbing a catch to backward point. Pant is furious with himself

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: RK Bhui
commentary: appeal for catch down the leg side, the umpire calls it a wide, and PBKS review it. This is fired into the pads, Bhui gets inside it, looks for a tickle fine to fine leg, and UltraEdge confirms he has gloved it. A second catch decision successfully reviewed by PBKS

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: T Stubbs
commentary: looks for the inside-out chip over extra cover, but again the lack of turn for Chahar perhaps means he ends up hitting it much straighter than desired. Shashank makes a good run to his left from long-off and completes a diving catch. And credit where it's due: this ball does drift in to hit him on the inner half of the bat

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: AR Patel
commentary: Close call on the run-out. The third umpire comes in. Short of a length, slower ball, angling in, Axar bunts it into the leg side, wants a second to keep strike but the substitute fielder Tanay's throw from deep square is on the money. Axar is caught short. No dive either

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: Sumit Kumar
commentary: now Arsh goes full, 134ks, seam slanting towards slip, and there is a bit of movement in the air to take the edge on the attempted big hit from Sumit

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: Abishek Porel

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: Kuldeep Yadav
commentary: finally tries the yorker, ends u bowling a low full toss, hit down to long-on for one. They try the second but Kuldeep ends up sacrificing himself

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: S Dhawan
commentary: Ishant rattles middle stump! He wins the battle of the Delhiites. Dhawan danced down, looked premeditated, and tried to heave across the line. Looked to have bounced lower than Dhawan expected. The 137ks ball zipped past him. Ishant's off in celebration.

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: JM Bairstow
commentary: Has Ishant tipped the ball in follow-through to run Bairstow out? Yeah, poor YJB. This was more unlucky though and he resigns with a smile while walking back. Was a slow ball into the pitch to which Prabhsimran charged and cuffed with a cross-ish bat. It poured along the pitch, Ishant went low to the right and got just a fingertip to it. Smart replays with multiple angles confirms and it and YJB, diving back, couldn't make it in time.

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: Prabhsimran Singh
commentary: Kuldeep gives it air and reaps rewards. Googly at 83ks is full and outside off, Prabhsimran tried to thrash it over the fielder but found Warner at long-on. Looked to have dipped a bit

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: SM Curran
commentary: Heaves across the line, Curran misses but not Khaleel. Offcutter on a length, lands outside off and comes back in. Curran was too early on the shot and it hit top of off. Preity Zinta applauds and is all smiles as Curran walks back

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: JM Sharma
commentary: Another appeal for stumping. Pant is all smiles. Is Jitesh walking? Sent upstairs. Was a length ball down leg, Jitesh went for the expansive reverse sweep. He missed it and was mid-jump and out of the crease. Meanwhile, Pant lunged low, stretched his upper body as far forward as he could and pushed the ball into the stumps. That oughta reaffirm thoughts around his keeping

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: LS Livingstone

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: Shashank Singh
commentary: Shashank has been bounced out first ball, Khaleel on a hat-trick. Pacy and at the armpit, the batter was done for pace and cramped for room as he tried to pull. Ball popped off the glove for Pant to take a dolly. Khaleel and Pant share a glance of understanding, this seems to be a plan coming off

venue: Maharaja Yadavindra Singh International Cricket Stadium, Mullanpur
name: Harpreet Brar
PD Salt
commentary: Salt swings to leg, but holes out to Jansen in the deep! Salt has shaken his last after giving the KKR fans a taste. Stepped away as Markande pushed one down the leg side, didn't quite get hold of his shot - but it still needed good work from Jansen running around to his right and diving full length for the catch

name: SP Narine
commentary: banged into the deck, Salt fends it away to backward point... and Narine has run himself out looking for one! Direct hit from Shahbaz Ahmed and he's nowhere in the frame! Salt had no intention of running there but Narine got about halfway down before noticing. Barely bothered to try and make his ground, with Jansen lurking to complete the run-out if needed

name: VR Iyer
commentary: larruped... straight to cover! Bit of a slot ball, really, and Iyer was looking to cash in with a hard-handed drive. But he couldn't have picked out the fielder better, Jansen staying low to clutch the ball to his chest. Second wicket of the evening for SRH

name: SS Iyer
commentary: chipped to mid-off! Superb take above his head by Cummins, and SRH have taken a third wicket inside the powerplay. Full from Natarajan and Shreyas was looking to loft it over the off side, almost cleared the man on the edge of the ring... but his opposite number is a tall bloke and reels in the catch. First down payment on that INR 20.5 crore fee from Cummins

name: N Rana
commentary: googly, Rana reverses... straight to backward point! Simple head-height catch for Tripathi and Rana can only offer a rueful smile as he walks off. Funky stuff fails to land, Markande strikes with his third ball. KKR slip deeper into the hole

name: Ramandeep Singh
commentary: chipped to cover, Cummins strikes! Hit high on the bat as he looked to drive on the up, well held by Markande diving across to his right. Ramandeep won't be taking this deep. The KKR recovery takes a hit

name: RK Singh
commentary: top-edged in the slog, taken at long-on! Rinku knows he has to go (or get Russell on strike). He opts for the former and holes out to Markram a few yards in off the rope

name: MA Agarwal
commentary: taken at deep backward square leg! Harshit offers a stare to Agarwal, who walks back, but not without looking back at Harshit! Short delivery at sharp pace around off, as he gets good bounce. Agarwal pulls but off the higher side of the bat. The longer side of the boundary comes into play, as Rinku takes it low

name: Abhishek Sharma
commentary: taken at fine leg! The man in the deep had to move a few steps to his left, and end at where an imaginary straightish fine leg would have been. Russell dug one a short at Abhishek, with the ball climbing nicely towards the batter's throat on middle and leg. He went for the pull, but top-edged it, with the extra pace getting the ball to zip through off the pitch

name: RA Tripathi
commentary: taken at fine leg! Narine strikes after being economical all day. Tripathi keeps attempting the sweep, and finds the fielder on this occasion. His struggle ends at a run-a-ball 20. The ball was again full, as Tripathi went slogging across the line

name: AK Markram
commentary: nabbed at deep midwicket! He had to take a few steps forward, and then bend to take it low. Rinku was the fielder there. Varun bowled full and on the stumps, as Markram went slog sweeping across the line, but ended up playing down the longer side of the ground. He departs, as SRH's required rate keeps rising

name: H Klaasen
shortText: c Suyash Sharma b Harshit Rana
commentary: great catch by Suyash! Someone listen to the deafening roar at Eden. Suyash, placed at short third, had to half-turn around while moving back and keeping his eyes on the ball. It arrived on him over his right shoulder, and he tumbled to take it. Another slower ball from Harshit, as he rolls his fingers over it. Bowls on a hittable length, though, and just outside off. Klaasen has a go at it aiming for the leg side, but plays early and gets it off a top edge

name: Abdul Samad
commentary: straight to deep midwicket! The fielder was placed right on the edge of the rope, and that arrived at a comfortable height, in front of his stomach. It was a full toss which was dipping just outside off, as Samad wasn't able to time his swing. He waited for a few seconds to confirm if it wasn't an above-waist no-ball or not, before heading back. But he's asked to wait, as the umpires take a look again. And replays confirm it arrived at him just below the waist, so it is not a no-ball

name: Shahbaz Ahmed
shortText: c SS Iyer b Harshit Rana
commentary: finds long-on! The crowd at Eden suddenly wakes up from sleep. Shahbaz falls, leaving this on the knife's edge. Harshit went on the shorter side of a length, while angling it across. The ball arrived around middle and off, as Shahbaz shaped to launch it down the ground but mistimed the shot for a simple catch for Shreyas

name: YBK Jaiswal
commentary: Clothed to mid-on and Jaiswal's distraught. Mohsin has shelled a few dollars but goes pace-on, into the pitch to hurry the in-form youngster. He went though with the shot but could only pop it straight to the man. The pitch has been on the slower side so far but this ball steered away from that trend.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: Nicked off on the flashing cover drive. Naveen is pumped! Excellent low catch from Rahul too. Was very full, there for the drive, but it's never as straightforward with Naveen's angles. Delivered from wide of the crease, it came in towards fifth stump, was coming back in. Buttler buckled his back knee and tried muscling it. The sound of the nick was like a stick breaking, it hovered low to Rahul's right. He was wrong-footed, as the first step was to the leg side, but he then flung himself low and timed the gather well.

name: R Parag
commentary: Tries doing something similar but holes out to deep-backward square. Was a shortish ball, 119ks, just outside off, Parag tried dragging it across with a pull, top edged it and Hooda took a dolly. Excellent 93-run stand though

name: SO Hetmyer
commentary: Appeal, given. Hetmyer reviews. Think it was caught behind even though Rahul dislodged the stumps while lifting his hand in celebration. Length ball landed in line and turned away, the lid-less Hetmyer's front foot was well in front of the crease and he tried to defend with a straight bat. Hawk-Eye shows there was a feather, much to Hetmyer's surprise. Rahul and Bishnoi are delighted, LSG are pulling it back

name: Q de Kock
commentary: taken at fine leg! This is pretty much a gift from de Kock for Boult, who offers a wry smile. Boult bowled this on the fuller side of a length, angling it in and pitching outside leg. De Kock went clipping it with the line, only to find the fielder positioned bang where he hit it. Burger took it with a reverse cup to get into the action right away

name: KL Rahul
commentary: taken at deep point! The pendulum swings late into the game. Sandeep bowls a wide line to Rahul, with the length being there to be hit. But Rahul went lofting far away from his body. Jurel had to take a few steps forward to catch that, and he did well in the end to send Rahul back

name: D Padikkal
commentary: bowled him! This one keeps low after the previous one hammered his helmet. The ball hits the top of middle, and the stump is flattened. Boult went slightly on the shorter side of a length this time, while angling it into the left-hander. The ball pitched on or about off stump, and came back in while not entirely taking off from the pitch. Padikkal had shaped to swipe - perhaps seeing the length - and so it was too late by the time he tried to bend to keep that out

name: A Badoni
commentary: spooned to mid-off! Buttler sees the ball dying on to him, and takes a low catch. Burger leaving Royals' mouths spicy already. He bowled on a length, while shaping it across the right-hander and arriving outside off. Badoni went lofting seeing the length, but couldn't time his shot, and found the man inside the circle

name: DJ Hooda
commentary: nabbed at deep midwicket! Chahal strikes straight away. Jurel was actually placed a good few steps into the field of play, and had to take some steps back to gobble it in front of his stomach. Chahal tossed one up to invite Hooda, with the ball being fullish and outside off. Hooda skipped down and heaved, but it came off the inside half of the bat

name: MP Stoinis
commentary: finds Jurel at deep midwicket! Ashwin went with the carrom ball, on a length on middle and leg. Stoinis had his front leg out of the way, and went hammering for a big hit. But Jurel ended up grabbing another catch, as he came a few steps forward

name: WP Saha
commentary: And you wonder why he didn't open the bowling! Yorker from wide of the crease, and it is searing into the base of off and middle. Saha is wrongfooted and he cannot bring the bat down in time. The poles light up and Saha is gone.

name: Shubman Gill
commentary: this is why IPL teams still back Piyush Chawla! He has the knack of taking wickets and he has delivered with a massive scalp. Chawla lets a quicker one rip, and Gill comes down the track to hit him over long on. But Gill's shot doesn't have the distance and Rohit takes a simple catch on the line

name: B Sai Sudharsan
commentary: full ball on middle, and he flicks it well to the leg side. In fact, too well! Straight to the fielder from deep backward square leg running in. A second diving catch from Tilak tonight

name: Azmatullah Omarzai
commentary: holes out at deep midwicket! And Coetzee celebrates in his trademark fashion with a big roar. Cross-seamed good length ball on off and Omarzai attempts to slog a shot over cow corner. But the leg-side is the bigger side over here at the Narendra Modi Stadium and Tilak composes himself in the deep to close out the catch

name: DA Miller
commentary: easy for Hardik at mid off running back! Bumrah starts off with the slower ball, fullish on off. Miller wants to loft it over mid off but then cannot change his momentum. Meets the ball too early and the ball pops off the bat's face and lobs towards mid off

name: R Tewatia
commentary: a stunning catch at deep square leg diving forward! Naman Dhir the fielder there. Coetzee bowls a shin-high full toss around leg and Tewatia tried to dropkick a shot over the leg side. But Dhir covers a lot of ground running in and commits to the forward drive! "I can see the fingers underneath," says the TV umpire, so Tewatia must go

name: Ishan Kishan
commentary: Has he nicked it? He has! Pulls his length back and pitches it around middle and off. The ball is going away from Kishan who pokes at it and gets a feather through to Saha. Omarzai has a wicket in his first over in the IPL!

name: RG Sharma
commentary: Rohit misses the sweep and the umpire raises his finger! Full outside off and angling in. Rohit can't connect. Big appeal and given immediately. Rohit reviews it. Was impact outside off? Impact in front of off and that's shown to be crashing into middle stump. No fifty for Rohit Sharma, but a very good knock nonetheless. Sai Kishore also gets his reward for a good spell

name: Naman Dhir
commentary: Big appeal for lbw, but the umpire doesn't give it. Gill chooses to review! It's on a length outside off and seams in sharply. Stays low to beat the bat as Dhir looks to swing across the line. Hit on the thigh on his back foot. And that's crashing into middle and leg according to ball tracking! Entertaining cameo comes to an end. And Omarzai ends his second over well after conceding 21 runs off it!

name: D Brevis
commentary: This time Mohit holds on! The pressure tells. Brevis falls for 46. 108kph delivery dug in short outside off. Brevis flat-bats it straight to Mohit who holds on at waist height. Brevis throws his head up in disgust. Is there a twist still in the waiting?

name: NT Tilak Varma
commentary: What a comeback from Spencer Johnson! Tilak flicks it straight to deep backward square! Spencer Johnson is pumped. Sub fielder Abhinav Manohar is pumped. This was full and angling into Tilak who moved across as he looked to flick it, but he can't get the elevation or the placement. Hit straight to the fielder. First IPL wicket for Spencer Johnson!

name: TH David
commentary: Brilliant catch by David Miller! Mohit goes for another slower bouncer, this time cramping David for room. He swivels as he looks to pull and gets it off the top edge. Miller has to run in from deep midwicket and dives forward to grab that. What a big wicket that is!

name: HH Pandya
commentary: And there ends Hardik's cameo! Short ball, cramping Hardik who goes for a pull and he only manages to top edge it down Tewatia's throat at long-on. He takes a rather simple catch and Hardik has to go.

name: G Coetzee
commentary: Top edge and it's taken! Bouncer on middle at 137kph, Coetzee miscues the pull and it goes high in the air. Spencer claims it, gets under it and holds on to it comfortably. What a brilliant 19th over from him after an expensive start to his debut! Sensational stuff!

name: PP Chawla
commentary: Straight to Rashid Khan at deep midwicket! Short ball angled across him does the trick. Piyush connected with the pull but couldn't get any elevation on it. Rashid catches it just above head height running back and Umesh Yadav is on a hat-trick!

name: S Dhawan
commentary: Two wickets in two balls! Dhawan holes out to long-off and RCB players are absolutely pumped! This is tossed up outside off and spinning away from Dhawan as he looks to go inside out. Miscues it to Kohli down the ground who takes a simple catch. That's the set batter gone

name: JM Bairstow
commentary: Skied and gone! Great comeback for Siraj. Bairstow swipes at a length ball. The bat turns in his hand as he hits it and it goes up. Kohli settles under it coming in from cover and takes it with no fuss

name: Prabhsimran Singh
commentary: Goes for another big shot and perishes! The ball bounces quite sharply from a length as Prabhsimran looks to slog. Gets a top edge high in the air and to Rawat's left and the keeper makes no mistake

name: LS Livingstone
commentary: Joseph gets the big wicket of Livingstone! Joseph bowls it short and wide and Livingstone looks to cut it away. Gets a thick edge through to the keeper. That's a big breakthrough delivered by one of their marquee signings!

name: SM Curran
commentary: What a brilliant catch! Take a bow, Anuj Rawat! Dayal directs a bouncer at Curran, who looks to pull but was cramped for room. Ends up gloving it. Rawat sticks his right arm up as he jumps in the air and plucks it out of the air. And that will be all for Sam Curran today. A few boundaries this over, but overall a fantastic spell from Yash Dayal. And he has another delivery to go!

name: JM Sharma
commentary: Short ball does the trick again! Second bouncer of the over, outside off. Jitesh looks to slap it on the off side but it goes high in the air. Anuj Rawat has been excellent with the gloves today and again, he makes no mistake. But wait! They are checking if it hit the Spider-Cam! But no reprieve for Jitesh after a check by the umpire. Seems to not have had any contact with the camera or the wires

name: V Kohli
commentary: Slashed, taken at wide third! That is field placement at its best! Harpreet was somewhere between deep third and deep-backward point and got a low catch in front. Kohli made room and tried to lift the 135ks full ball, couldn't get the placement right or the power to clear the man. He leans on his bat in disappointment. PBKS ahead now?

name: F du Plessis
commentary: Skied to mid-on, Rabada gets his former skipper. Full ball at 137ks at the stumps, Faf tried getting under it and launching it down the ground, got it off the bottom edge. The open stance doesn't help as he can't transfer the weight forward. He knew he was gone right away. Easy enough catch for Curran, who is pumped

name: C Green
commentary: Appeal for caught behind, there's a small chat about whether the was catch. Looked like the umpire raised his finger but it is actually sent upstairs. Jitesh dove to the right and took it low, ball went straight in the gloves. Was a wide 137ks length ball that was around the offside tramline. Green tried heaving it square on the offside but even his reach wasn't enough

name: RM Patidar
commentary: Darted into middle, beats Patidar's attempted hoick over midwicket! Length ball, coming in with the angle, was an arm ball. Pace in the late 90ks. Patidar couldn't shift gears after being promoted.

name: GJ Maxwell
commentary: Maxwell makes room and chops it on! This is why fingerspinners bowl stump to stump in T20s. Maxwell made room to open up the offside but underedged onto ground and back on to middle. 90ks. Like after the last wicket, Harpreet has a thigh-five and spreads his arms wide

name: Anuj Rawat
commentary: Slower one hits pad, that looked dead. Given too, Rawat reviews. Offcutter at 108ks, was the turn taking it too far? Impact seems to have been on middle and leg. Rawat was on the front foot and got hit under the knee roll after being beaten on the flick. Dhawan has a word with Curran while Hawk-Eye loads. That might not have been a cutter, almost looks like a back of handed. Chetan, our scorer, says it might be a googly. What does it say now? Clipping leg stump, decision stands.

name: RD Gaikwad
commentary: Huge appeal for caught behind and the umpire has given it. Gaikwad is walking off as well. Back of a length ball angling across the batter, who looks for a pull, gets an inside edge with the ball going to the keeper. That's a rather important wicket

name: R Ravindra
commentary: Oh, is Rachin stumped there? His reaction and Saha's reaction seems to suggest so. Oh, yeah, he is gone. Was a quicker length ball on leg stump, he gets a thick inside edge through his leg. Don't think Rachin knew how far or where exactly the ball went and ventured out of his crease. Saha was quick to whip off the bails to finds Rachin short

name: AM Rahane
commentary: Sai Kishore gets his man. The Chennai boy strikes at home. Was pushed quicker on middle, and that turned just a little bit as well. Rahane jumps down looking to go across the line. Misses, and Saha does the rest.

name: S Dube
commentary: Mistimed and Rashid gets his man! Googly right across Dube and away from his arc outside off. Was at the tramline. Dube looks to go after him, gets it right of the bottom of blade as the ball balloons straight up for extra cover to take a simple catch

name: Sameer Rizvi
commentary: Straight down long-on's throat! On-pace full ball on off stump. He gets under it, and looks to go over long-on. Gets it off the bottom of the bat with Miller making no mistake.

name: RA Jadeja
commentary: Pace off and there is a run out. Slower back of a length ball, Jadeja pulls to deep midwicket. Mitchell hares back for a second, but Jadeja isn't going anywhere. Saha casually whips off the bails and Jadeja is deemed out after the TV umpire has a look

name: WP Saha
commentary: straight to deep square leg! The fielder was present there for the short ball, and the ploy has paid off. Short of good length ball coming into Saha. He bravely goes for the pull. Drags the shot behind square, and it doesn't have the height to go all the way.

name: Shubman Gill
commentary: celebrappeal from Chahar, and given by the umpire lbw! Gill reviews. This is a good length ball on off and Gill looks to play a check-pull in front of square, but the ball stays marginally low and hits him on the back leg. Will height save Gill? Tense GT fans in the crowd.... and that's three reds! The Titans captain is gone for a five-ball eight

name: B Sai Sudharsan
commentary: full ball on off stump. Sudharsan shows aggression by trying to lift it over long on, but checks it in the last moment. Doesn't have the distance to clear Rizvi at long on and he takes a simple catch near the boundary line.

name: V Shankar
commentary: vintage Dhoni! Dives to his right and he gets both hands to it! Full ball on a fourth-stump line. Shankar tries to drive straight but the ball takes the edge, and Dhoni pounces onto it in legendary fashion

name: DA Miller
commentary: Rahane with an athletic effort to take a stunning catch! Deshpande searches for the yorker on leg stump. Miller clears his front leg and tries to dropkick a flick through midwicket, but Rahane attacks the ball from cow corner, running in, and then dives forward to take a low catch! Stunning catch

name: Azmatullah Omarzai
commentary: this time Rachin takes the catch! Redeems himself. Short and wide ball. Omarzai tries to slap it over backward point but ends up flat-batting a shot high up in the air. Rachin runs across from extra cover to cover and brings out the reverse-cup catching technique again...however, this time it sticks! Takes a tumble on the followthrough but sports a smile as the ball is firmly in his grasp

name: R Tewatia
commentary: full ball wider outside off stump. Tewatia shapes up to clobber it over long off but it doesn't have the power. Rachin stays on the long-off boundary line, and takes a simple catch

name: Rashid Khan
commentary: that's...... gone! Good length ball on leg, and this is the cutter in fact. Ball scrambles Rashid as he clears the front leg and tries to club it over the leg side. Totally mistimed, and Rachin is in the action again at deep square leg

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: MA Agarwal
commentary: David makes no mistake this time. Hardik goes short, just outside off. Agarwal goes for the pull but ends up top-edging it towards mid-on. A much simpler catch this time for David

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: TM Head
commentary: Plan B has worked. Coetzee bowls a length ball but more importantly keeps it away from Head who had to reach out for it. Ends up hitting it to deep-backward point where Dhir pouches it

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Abhishek Sharma
commentary: Chawla finally provides a breakthrough. This was bowled at 112.8kph. Abhishek went for another six but was a bit hurried. As a result, he doesn't get the timing right and Dhir settles under it at deep midwicket

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: AK Markram

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: H Klaasen

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: RG Sharma
commentary: High in the air, no reprieve this time. Rohit has to walk back. Cummins gets the big wicket! Back of length delivery seams in slightly from outside off. Rohit is looking for the pull but gets a top edge that goes miles in the air. Abhishek Sharma has to take a few steps in from deep backward square and he makes no mistake as he catches it falling forward

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Ishan Kishan
commentary: Kishan holes out at deep midwicket! Shahbaz tosses it up wider, Kishan goes for the slog sweep again and ends up not hitting it cleanly. The ball goes high but doesn't have the distance. Aiden Markram takes it backtracking near the boundary

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Naman Dhir
commentary: And there is the breakthrough! Slapped straight to cover! On a length around middle and off, Naman makes room and looks to get it over cover. Can't get the elevation and captain Cummins grabs it above head height

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: NT Tilak Varma
commentary: And Cummins gets the well set Tilak! Slower bouncer angled across Tilak. He tried to fetch it from well outside off with a pull and miscues it. Mayank Agarwal comes in from deep midwicket and holds on!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: HH Pandya
commentary: And Hardik Pandya has to go! Unadkat is all laughs. SRH know they now all but have it in the bag. Cutter dug into the pitch, seaming away. Hardik goes for a pull but can only top edge it. Easy peasy lemon squeezy for Heinrich Klaasen

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: TH David

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: R Shepherd
YBK Jaiswal
commentary: Is that one stump out the ground or two? Looks like off stump was flattened and middle rattled. The flying bails was shiver-inducing. Seam-bowling special. 141ks on a length, angling in from around the wicket, decked in to cramp Jaiswal for room on the flick, ball ricocheted off the bat onto the stumps.

name: JC Buttler
commentary: Beaten on the reverse, lbw appeal turned down. Kuldeep took the matter, and literally Rishabh's hands, into his own and signalled the T. Where did this pitch though? Buttler tried playing it on the up, got beaten and ball hit just under the knee-roll, outer-half of the pad. It has pitched in line and Kuldeep might as well have Hawk-Eye tech embedded in him cos the ball is projected to land in line and go on to smash leg peg. It landed around a back of length too, which makes his conviction look even better. Buttler tried to break out of his struggle but perishes in the attempt

name: SV Samson
commentary: Guided to the keeper! Khaleel's around-the-wicket-angle works. He's cramped Samson for room, who tried to back away and chop the 141ks into-the-pitch ball through point. Ends up nicking it to Pant. Khaleel's jubilant, DC's new-ball bowlers have made it their powerplay.

name: R Ashwin
commentary: Ashwin tries to clear deep midwicket but can't. 95ks length ball angling in, he saw it in his half and tried went for a stand-up slog sweep. Got a decent chunk but not enough to clear Stubbs, who took it and swivelled back, the step was within the cushion. Ashwin's given RR's innings some impetus though

name: DC Jurel
commentary: Paddled onto off stump, that's a rare visual. Jurel picked the fast, full ball from outside the offside tramline, seemed to have middled it but unintentionally sent the bails on a sexy-looking flight. Second of those on the night after Jaiswal's dismissal. Nortje is pumped

name: DA Warner
shortText: c Sandeep Sharma b Avesh Khan
commentary: Flying Sandeep ends Warner's stay. No fifty for Warner but the umpires want to take another look. Length ball angling away, he once again flashes hard at it and gets a thick outside edge. Sandeep at short third moves to his right and leaps to catch that. It is a clean one and the Capitals opener has to walk back

name: MR Marsh
commentary: Gone through the gate! Missile on a length, swinging back in a touch at 145.8kph. Marsh tries to run it down to third but is done in by the inward movement and is knocked over. The after-holi pink hair of Burger sway as he celebrates with full vigour

name: RK Bhui
commentary: Bhui bounced out! Burger bangs it short at 138.5kph - it seemed more like 158.3! - Bhui only tries to fend it away. The ball gets big on him and lobs off his front glove. The easiest of catches for Samson who takes a few steps ahead and pouches it. Jaipur roars

name: RR Pant
commentary: Chahal strikes! Lands it on a shortish length, angling it wider outside, 91.1kph. Pant has to wait a bit and looks to cut but gets a faint lower edge. Samson does the rest

name: Abishek Porel
commentary: Porel perishes now. Chahal tosses it up and throws it wide outside off. He knows Porel will charge down again, and he has to fetch the ball from well outside off. Miscues it straight down long-off's throat

name: F du Plessis
commentary: And Rana has his revenge next ball! He is off and running in celebrations with his arms stretched. He bowls an offcutter on a length well outside off. Du Plessis once again goes for the scoop over short fine leg but couldn't counter the change of pace. Hits it straight to Starc in the circle. Early strike for KKR

name: C Green
commentary: Knocked him over! Six-and-out once again tonight. Russell fires it full on the pads, 131.4kph, Green looks to flick it away but misses. The ball ricochets off the back pad and the stumps light up. Russell is pumped up and so are KKR

name: GJ Maxwell
commentary: Finally a KKR fielder holds on to a catch. Maxwell departs and Narine strikes. Lands one on a length outside off, gets it to bounce a bit more. Maxwell looks to go hard and gets a top edge towards deep point. Rinku runs in a fair bit and catches it, kisses the ball after that

name: RM Patidar
commentary: Catching practice for Rinku. Back of a length around off, 112.7kph, Patidar has to manufacture the power in his heave across the line. The bat turns in his hands and he hits it straight to deep midwicket. 100th IPL wicket for Dre Russ

name: Anuj Rawat
commentary: Soft dismissal. Full offcutter outside off, Rawat looks to go over the off side. Gets a thick outside edge that carries low to Salt behind.

name: KD Karthik
commentary: Moves across, and misses! Length ball going away, he does not make contact. They look to steal a bye but Salt hits the stumps at the striker's end with DK not making it in. RCB end on 182 for 6

name: PD Salt
commentary: buckethands Green grabs that! Short ball angling into him and Salt goes for a pull. But that's been drilled straight to the man who is guarding the deep square leg boundary. Big roar from Vyshak and Salt is gone for 30

name: SP Narine
commentary: yorker, on off stump, and this crashes into the base of off stump! Wicket soon after the time-out and Narine will not get a landmark fifty in his 500th T20. He was too slow to bring the bat down, but to be fair, he's done his job tonight

name: VR Iyer
commentary: holes out straight after fifty and Dayal has something to celebrate. Pace-off length ball outside off. Venkatesh tries to tonk a pull over cow corner but this time he drags the shot. Kohli makes no mistake

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Q de Kock
commentary: And he strikes straightaway! Bangs it in short outside off, de Kock goes for the pull but gets a top edge. Jitesh gets under it and makes no mistake

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KL Rahul
commentary: Arshdeep has his revenge! Rahul looks to dab away a length ball going across him, opens the face but steers it to Bairstow's left at backward point. The Englishman reacts sharply and sends Rahul packing for a 9-ball 15

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: D Padikkal
commentary: Hit straight to mid-off! Padikkal looks to back away and slap this length ball away. He hit it well, he hit it hard, but he hit it too close to Dhawan, who just moves to his right to gobble that up

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: MP Stoinis
commentary: Knocks him over! Rahul Chahar bowls this on a length on middle, quicker and flatter. Stoinis went for the pull and missed and the ball went in with the angle to hit leg stump. Just as Stoinis got going, he has to go!

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: N Pooran
commentary: Pooran drags it onto his stumps! Pooran is disgusted with himself. This is full and way wide, Pooran looks for a big shot and ends up getting a big inside edge onto the stumps. That's a massive wicket for Kings. Pooran was looking very deadly!

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: A Badoni
commentary: Holes out at long-on. Slower ball, full outside off, and Badoni can only lob it up to Bairstow in the deep. He struggled today and falls for 8 off 10. This was bowled at 86kph!

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KH Pandya

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Ravi Bishnoi
commentary: Two in two for Curran! Slower ball again, 109kph, dug in short. Bishnoi went for the pull but could only find the deep square leg fielder

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Mohsin Khan
commentary: A bit of a mix-up and Mohsin is run-out. Krunal drives another full toss straight into the non-striker's stumps. Mohsin had taken off for a run after seeing the ball hit the stumps, but Krunal isn't interested. Harshal is quick to collect the ball and uproot one of the stumps

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Naveen-ul-Haq

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: S Dhawan
commentary: Bumper is tickled to the keeper. Dhawan can't close out the chase. This landed around fourth, Dhawan swung his head outside off and tried to hook it almost, feathered it to QDK, who wasn't fazed by the dipping ball and took a good catch to the left. Dhawan ends with a SR of 140 but I'd say it's hard to blame him for not going harder during the Mayank's whirlwind spell

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: JM Bairstow
commentary: Mayank's pace breaks the partnership 143ks. Bairstow started making room and Mayank followed him, went into the pitch, found the top edge off the pull. Was a length ball on top of leg, Bairstow was deep in the crease and was hurried despite seeming to have planned the shot in advance. Ball sailed three-fourth of the way out, Stoinis ran in and took a sliding catch

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Prabhsimran Singh
commentary: Ballooned pull to mid-on, 147ks. Short and over midde, rose around rib-height, Prabhsimran cleared the front leg and tried forcing it but clothed it straight to Naveen. Pace doing pace things. Good cameo from the batter though

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: JM Sharma
commentary: 141ks, Another pull us ballooned, Naveen takes another catch. Short into the pitch, rises around rib-height, Jitesh looked to go over midwicket but like a few other team-mates, got hurried. Naveen went from mid-on towards short midwicket to catch the top edged ball

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: LS Livingstone

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: SM Curran
commentary: Pull skied, catch taken at mid-on, Mohsin has two in two. Another slower bumper, just under shoulder-height just outside off, Curran tried leathering the pull but got a top edge. No sighters and no second chances - death overs doing its thing

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Shashank Singh
TM Head
commentary: Noor strikes gold for the Titans! It's the googly again, pitching just outside off stump, Head goes for the slog sweep but completely misses it, and the furniture is rattled.

name: MA Agarwal
commentary: The pressure has told on Mayank! Shorter length ball, 137ks, tucking up Mayank, who goes for the swivel pull but the line had tucked him up so he couldn't get a free swing going, Nalkande pockets a simple catch at deep square leg

name: Abhishek Sharma
commentary: Soft dismissal. Slower ball, on a length on off stump, Abhishek is too early into an attempted off drive, so he can only slice that straight to Gill at extra cover. Completely lost his balance on that shot, the bottom hand came off the bat as well.

name: AK Markram
commentary: Markram's timed that one too well, and that is his undoing! Length ball from Umesh, Markram plays the on-drive aerially, hits it too well, Rashid runs forward, slides and pouches it. The home fans are ecstatic!

name: H Klaasen
commentary: Massive moment in the game! Rashid bids goodbye to Klaasen. Flatter delivery, on a length and attacking the stumps, Klaasen looks to go back and mow it over midwicket, misses it and sees his stumps rearranged. Rashid has his hands aloft, Gill is ecstatic, and rightfully so.

name: Shahbaz Ahmed
commentary: back of the hand slower ball again, Shahbaz gets absolutely no timing on it, and ends up clonking it straight up in the air, Tewatia runs in from long-on to complete an easy catch

name: Abdul Samad
commentary: slower short ball again, Cummins again doesn't time the pull shot well enough, and can only find square leg. They keep running off that last ball, and Samad ends up being run out

name: Washington Sundar
commentary: Off cutter this time, dug in short, Washington connects nicely with the pull, but doesn't get enough power behind it and hits it straight to Rashid at deep midwicket. Samad is disappointed at being starved of the strike here.

name: WP Saha
commentary: Change of ends works for Shahbaz. He went fuller side of length, 89ks, at the stumps. Saha lunged forward but had to reach too far forward as he tried to lift it over midwicket. Having to do it on the up didn't help. Ends up spooning it.

name: Shubman Gill
commentary: Gill holes out to long-on. Mistake in execution cos the ball was in his slot. Slow on leg, 89ks, he danced down and probably got too close to the pitch. Maybe he wanted to go wider. Markande and SRH will take that with both hands

name: B Sai Sudharsan
commentary: Pulled, holes out to deep midwicket. Was a length ball that was hit from deep in the crease, Sudharsan tried to clear Abhishek but a sliding catch was taken in the end

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: PP Shaw
commentary: length outside off. Shaw goes for the cut but gets only an outside edge and Dhoni makes no mistake

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: DA Warner
commentary: what a catch! Slower one, full on the stumps. Warner goes for the reverse scoop and hits it alright but Pathirana jumps to his right and grabs it mid-air and one-handed

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: RR Pant
commentary: full outside off. Pant goes aerial but ends up slicing it as the bottom hands comes off. It goes miles in the air and Ruturaj Gaikwad, who was settling under it at long-off, had to dive to his left to pouch it

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: MR Marsh
commentary: 150.4kph and the middle stump is out of the ground. An excellent yorker that moves in a touch to beat Marsh's bat and rattle the woodwork

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: T Stubbs
commentary: off stump is flat on the ground this time. Another searing yorker, at 149kph. Stubbs had no clue as the ball crashed into the off and middle stumps

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: AR Patel

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: Abishek Porel

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: RD Gaikwad
commentary: seams back in, nicked behind! The extra ball in the over brings a wicket, and it is CSK captain Gaikwad to fall. Expansive drive to a length ball but it only succeeded in feathering an inside edge through to Pant. Khaleel gets a big early breakthrough for DC

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: R Ravindra
commentary: short, this time he connects... and a mishit to mid-on ends Ravindra's stay! That had been coming, second wicket for Khaleel. It was all yellow for Ravindra, but not in the good way. Couldn't get his rhythm and then finally chips a pull straight up. There were two fielders competing to take the catch but in the end Stubbs makes it safe with a tumbling effort running across from mid-off

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: AM Rahane
commentary: plinked to long-on, Mukesh strikes! Perfectly executed slower ball and Rahane holes out. Just a little offcutter wide of the stumps and there was no pace for the batter to work with looking to go down the ground. Safely pouched several yards in from the rope. DC tightening their grip

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: DJ Mitchell
commentary: driven... straight back into the buckets! Axar stoops to his left and scoops up the catch, makes the breakthrough for DC. Mitchell hit that pretty well but couldn't keep on top of the bounce. Axar turns and spreads his arms wide to take the acclaim

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: S Dube
commentary: short with pace off, slapped to long-off! Stand and deliver from Dube but it's gone first class down the throat of Stubbs. Third wicket for Mukesh, who's only bowled seven balls so far

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: Sameer Rizvi
commentary: bounce, edged, taken! Lovely stuff from Mukesh, and Rizvi goes first ball! Searching line on off stump and he was looking to close the face, got a thick edge to short third where Khaleel held on to a sharp catch

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: RA Jadeja

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: MS Dhoni
Ishan Kishan
commentary: This is Test-match cricket, says Sanjay Manjrekar on air, and that's pretty much it. Bolt-upright seam, good - nay - perfect length. Lands around off, straightens off the deck and Kishan tries punching it straight. The movement finds the outside edge and the keeper takes it. A bit of extra bounce too that had Kishan hopping. Burger leaps in delight.

name: RG Sharma
commentary: Edged and taken first ball! What a ball to silence the crowd! 132ks, scrambled-seam, on a length, lands around off and goes through the channel. It opens up Rohit on the straight-bat defence and takes the outside edge. Low carry to Samson's right but he dives and takes it well

name: Naman Dhir
commentary: Lightning Boult strikes twice! Given out lbw but it's been reviewed. On a length again but this one comes in. Naman tried pushing it towards mid-on but the movement meant there was a big gap between bat and ball. Hit on the knee-roll while on the front foot. Hawk-Eye shows it'd go on to clip leg stump. Two in two to end the over. He'll be on a hat-trick for the start of his next over?

name: D Brevis
commentary: Loose shot, taken at short third! Three in four for the lightning Boult that strikes thrice. Length on fifth, Brevis' front stride to a ball angling away meant it was outside his reach for an off-drive.

name: NT Tilak Varma
commentary: RR don't have to worry about Tilak farming strike anymore as Chahal gets him with a wide ball. On a length, had him reach out. Might've even been wide had he left it but he committed to the cut. Googly too, which meant it spun away further, the edge was found and the ball ballooned to short third's left. Good leaping take from Ashwin

name: HH Pandya
commentary: Chahal has Hardik hole out! 86ks but flattish, landed around middle and leg and Hardik stood in the crease and tried to club it over long-on. Front leg was out of the way, could he have danced down to that? Got it off the bottom, Powell moved to the right and took a stumbling catch.

name: PP Chawla
commentary: Hetmyer takes a stunner at point. Reaches out to the right and takes it with both hands outstretched, around shoulder-height. Was not that short, around fifth stump and Chawla smashed it. Deep cut if it can be called one, was travelling fast. It's why Samson leapt over Hettie in delight in celebrations

name: TH David
commentary: David can't finish on a high. Burger goes into the pitch, angles in at the body. It's pulled from deep in the crease, flat and to Boult at the long-leg boundary, who takes it just while jogging to the right. Maybe David was expecting the slower one too there

name: G Coetzee
commentary: Softie to cover. Chahal winning the invitational with a 76ks legbreak. Fullish, lands around fifth and turns away a bit. Coetzee looked to drive on the up, didn't try and muscle it but ended up spooning it Hetmyer

name: YBK Jaiswal
commentary: Maphaka gets Jaiswal! First wicket in the IPL for the 17-year-old! Pitched up on a full length outside off and shaping away from Jaiswal, who pushes at it. Ends up lobbing it straight to David at cover

name: JC Buttler
commentary: Pulled straight to deep fine leg! Bouncer on off at 134kph, Buttler looks for the pull, but hits it flat and straight to Piyush Chawla who makes no mistake.

name: SV Samson
commentary: Samson chops on! Madhwal bowls it short of good length outside off, Samson looks for a cut with no foot movement. Gets an underedge onto the stumps. Can this be a turning point?

name: R Ashwin
commentary: Madhwal has his third! Short ball jags in from outside off. Ashwin looks to turn it leg side but gets a leading edge that goes high in the air. Tilak takes a good catch running back from backward point. Did well to settle under that skier. Madhwal strikes again in his last over

name: Q de Kock
commentary: taken at long-off by Dagar again! A full toss outside off, as it dips on to the batter this time too. Topley went for the back-of-the-hand slower ball. De Kock went lofting back down the ground, but ended up giving a comfortable catch to long-off coming a few steps to his left

name: KL Rahul
commentary: taken at extra cover! Dagar keeps his eyes on the ball, which Rahul sent ballooning off outside half of the bat, and took it in front of his chest. Maxwell pulled his length back to go short and slightly wide of off. Rahul was in the mood for more, and got his front leg out of the way in trying to swat it away. But there was good bounce for the bowler, and the ball skied up for a catch

name: D Padikkal
commentary: taken by Rawat running back! He turned around and started chasing the ball, going down on his haunches to take the ball which was dropping over his head, taking it just over his face. Rawat didn't get distracted by deep third running forward either. Siraj went for a back-of-a-length ball this time, landing it on leg. Padikkal cleared his front leg, and went for the pull, but only managed to get a top edge

name: MP Stoinis
commentary: taken by Dagar! He was placed at point, and saw the ball come on to his right, as he moved a few steps and grabbed with both hands. Maxwell strikes again, as he bowls short and wide of off. Stoinis had backed away early, so the line of the ball meant that it was quite wide of him. He eventually reached out for it, and ended up swatting to the fielder

name: A Badoni
shortText: c du Plessis b Yash Dayal
commentary: well taken by du Plessis! The ball was dropping over his right shoulder, as placed at extra cover, he tumbled across to his right while watching the ball well. Dayal went for a bouncer, angling it across, while also changing the pace. The ball rose rather sharply, and was very wide of off. Badoni still went swatting, but ended up getting it off the outside half of the bat

name: V Kohli
commentary: Siddharth has his man! Kohli skies it to backward point! Full outside off, Kohli was coming down the crowd and going for the big shot. He just gets a leading edge and the ball loops to backward point's left. Padikkal makes no mistake and Siddharth is pumped as the Chinnaswamy goes silent

name: F du Plessis
commentary: Direct hit! Faf clips a full ball at 153.2kph towards midwicket and takes off. Padikkal is quick to pick up the ball and with one stump to aim at, absolutely nails it with du Plessis caught well short of the crease

name: RM Patidar
commentary: Top edge goes high in the air. Devdutt Padikkal makes no mistake at deep square leg! It's banged in short, Patidar goes for the pull and skies it. Devdutt Padikkal had to move around to settle under it, but never took his eyes off it and ends up grabbing it to send Patidar back in the hut. Mayank has his third!

name: GJ Maxwell
commentary: Mayank Yadav has Maxwell! Pace does the trick. 151kph. Dug in on a length and Maxwell looks to swing it away. Slices it off the top edge. Pooran runs in from mid-on and pockets it. That's KGF back in the hut!

name: C Green
commentary: What a corker! Length ball outside off, straightens ever so little and Green is beaten for pace on the outside edge as the ball rams into the off stump before racing away to the boundary! Mayank Yadav is turning on the heat!

name: Anuj Rawat
commentary: Rawat falls. Stoinis goes short around off as he sees Rawat advancing. Gets cramped for room and gets it off high on the bat to mid-on. Pooran has to take a few steps forward before grabbing it. Rawat has struggled today and gets out without much impact in the end

name: MK Lomror
commentary: That should be game, set and match. Full outside off, he looks to go over long-off, but hits it too flat and Nicholas Pooran makes absolutely no mistake. Lomror's counterattack ends

name: KD Karthik
commentary: Gloved behind! That's that for DK. It's a back of length delivery angled into Karthik who wants to pull, but gets cramped for room and it pops up to Rahul

name: MJ Dagar
commentary: Goes high in the air, but lands in no man's land. But wait, there's a run-out! Lomror takes a full ball and skies it short of long-on. Pooran runs in gets the ball and was looking to throw it to the keeper but ends up hitting the stumps at the striker's end where Dagar is caught well short as he looked to go for a second but was sent back

name: Mohammed Siraj
commentary: Oh, Nicholas Pooran you beauty! Siraj lofts Naveen straight down the ground, Pooran runs across from long-on and throws himself at it and holds on tumbling forward. And LSG have bowled RCB out to register a 28-run win!

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: PD Salt
commentary: now taken by Stubbs at mid-off! So Salt's luck doesn't last long. He stands deep in the crease, and a bit outside leg, looking to loft at this pretty full ball angling into the stumps. I think he was done in by the rapid pace there, with the ball seemingly skidding through.

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: SP Narine
commentary: tickled to Pant! It was a soft dismissal. Narine falls to the bouncer. It pitched on off, and climbed on rather sharply towards Narine. He was standing after backing away, and looked to pull. But the extra bounce meant the ball took the top edge to the keeper, who took it with a reverse cup in front his face

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: A Raghuvanshi
commentary: ramped to deep third! Ishant Sharma seemed to be at a straightish deep third, rather. Nortje went for the short ball around sixth stump, and the ball rose considerably. So Raghuvanshi went ramping while using the pace and bounce, but found the fielder on the edge of the boundary

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: AD Russell
commentary: wow, superb ball! An inswinging yorker at 144kph floors Russell - literally! It lands on the base of middle and leg, as Russell looks to jam his bat down with a horizontal bat, but is late. It is too quick for him, and he ends up on his stomach on the pitch

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: SS Iyer
commentary: taken at mid-off! Shreyas falls to the short ball. Khaleel bowled outside off, as the ball almost seemed to have rushed through to Shreyas, who went pulling but got it off the top edge. Stubbs kept his eyes on the skied ball, and took it reverse cupped

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: RK Singh
commentary: ahh, taken at mid-on! But what a typical Rinku innings: an impact cameo at the death to demoralise the opposition. Nortje went for a dipping yorker around fifth stump, as Rinku almost squatted to try and chip that back. But he couldn't it away this time, as Warner took it over his head

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: VR Iyer

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: Ramandeep Singh
commentary: nabbed at extra cover! DC are striking late to check KKR. A slower ball this time from Ishant, who went short and pretty wide of off. Ramandeep went swatting far away from his body at what was a tenth-stump ball, but ended up getting the toe end of the bat to Shaw's left for a simple catch

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: MA Starc

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: DA Warner
commentary: chopped on! Starc gets the second Aussie too. Good length ball on a fifth-stump line. Warner doesn't have the width to cut but goes for it anyway. Under-edge onto the deck and into the stumps. Replay shows Starc changed his pace on the wicket ball

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: PP Shaw
commentary: can mid-on get there - yes! Varun Chakravarthy, not particularly known for his fielding, has taken a sensational low catch diving forward. Vaibhav bowls a fullish ball outside off, and the ball swings into Shaw. He tries mow it over mid-on, but mis-hits. The ball doesn't gather a lot of air, so Varun has to take the tough route of diving forward. Mission possible! They go to the TV umpire who confirms it is a clean catch.

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: MR Marsh
commentary: Mitchell gets Mitchell! And that is Starc's first IPL 2024 wicket. Marsh looks to drive this full ball from his body and generates a lot of power on that shot, but not the height, and Ramandeep at cover point intuitively sticks both hands out at the right time. Marsh's poor form continues

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: Abishek Porel
commentary: short ball too good for Porel! Simple catch for short fine leg. Arora aims for a short ball at Porel's head, and he tries the pull while taking his eyes of the ball. Knocks the youngster over with a classic tall fast bowler's dismissal

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: RR Pant
commentary: this time Shreyas holds onto a catch off Varun's bowling! Tossed up ball, a bit wider outside off. Turning away and Pant also tries to go inside out over cover. Throws all his energy behind it but the shot is sliced and Shreyas at cover calls for that nice and early

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: T Stubbs
commentary: Stubbs' innings is over as he can't clear Starc at deep backward square leg. Varun bowls a quicker one that lands outside leg, and Stubbs doesn't get enough room for his hands to go through the bat swing. Taken well inside the boundary line

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: AR Patel
commentary: Manish Pandey joins the action now! Runs in from long on and takes a catch inside the circle that was swirling by diving forward. Varun enticed Axar with a tossed up ball just outside off and he went for the glory shot. Mistimed, very high in the air, and there was little doubt on Pandey's catching technique

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: Sumit Kumar
commentary: To deep midwicket! Full ball on off and middle. Turning into Sumit. With only tailenders remaining, he goes for a big shot over the leg side, but does not have the distance on this occasion either. Time out

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: Rasikh Salam
commentary: And Vaibhav gets a third! Goes for the tried-and-tested method of bouncer to a lower-order batter. Gets a shoulder-high ball to Rasikh outside off and he slices the pull to the wicketkeeper

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: A Nortje
commentary: length ball around off. Pulled but without much power, and taken by Shreyas on the leg side inside the circle! KKR win by 106 runs

venue: Dr. Y.S. Rajasekhara Reddy ACA-VDCA Cricket Stadium, Visakhapatnam
name: I Sharma
WP Saha
commentary: 143ks. Skied, Dhawan takes it at mid-off. Fuller side of length, around middle stump, Saha tried turning it legside this time. Maybe go over the top, like he did last ball, but got a leading edge. Don't think he looked comfortable against high pace but 30 in three ain't too bad in the powerplay

name: KS Williamson
commentary: Extra bounce gets him, the cut is edged to backward point. 91ks, wide on a length, Harpreet probably inviting Kane to go down the ground again. He stayed in the crease and tried to carve it with decent power. In fact, the line was around fifth stump, Williamson made room and tried to open up the offside with a cut

name: B Sai Sudharsan
commentary: Has that been steered to the keeper? Jitesh goes big in appeal, Sudharsan walks. 128ks, shortish if not actually a bouncer. Line around fifth stump, height around the neck, the upper cut/ramp was attempted. He tried to go fine but got it off the cue end. Harshal did in fact put revs on it. Kudos to his fitness to bowl at that pace

name: V Shankar
commentary: No, Vijay tries to go for the boundary but flat bats it to long-off. Good catch by Brar, running in and takes it while sliding into the ground. Was shortish, slow and a touch wide.

name: S Dhawan
commentary: Chopped on! Ahmedabad roars. Length ball, angling away from Dhawan, he stands tall to punch it through cover. But the ball ricochets off the inside edge onto the stumps. Umesh strikes first ball and Titans are on the board. Kings' win percentage goes down from 26% to 19%

name: JM Bairstow
commentary: Cracker of a delivery! Noor is off. He tosses it up and lands it on a length outside leg. Bairstow completely misses the line of the ball and leaves a small gab between bat and pad. He was also on the move. That gap is enough for the ball to sneak through and deflect off the back pad to rattle the stumps. Another failure for YJB

name: Prabhsimran Singh
commentary: Flummoxed! Noor tosses up the googly around middle and off, Prabhsimran is early in backing away, and has made his mind to go across the line. All he manages is a top edge and Mohit at short third has hardly had to move. Kings slide steadily

name: SM Curran
commentary: Catching practice! Curran wanted to swivel and pull to exploit the space between deep square leg and long-on. But he does not manage to get the elevation. Omarzai bowls it on a shortish length on leg at 135.1kph, Curran swivels and hits it straight to Williamson at short midwicket

name: Sikandar Raza
commentary: Gonzo! The length ball does it for Mohit. Hard length, Raza backs away and looks to slap it over cover. Only manages a thin outside edge to the wicketkeeper. Is that the telling blow?

name: JM Sharma
commentary: Rashid gets a wicket off a full toss! He cannot believe it. Gill knows it is a bonus. They share a laugh. Jitesh cannot believe what he has done and is down on his haunches. He gives it his all and only skies it to Nalkande at deep midwicket. Kings still in the game but they need someone to stay in with Shashank. This is Rashid's 50th wicket for Titans

name: AR Sharma
commentary: And CAN YOU BELIEVE IT Nalkande strikes first ball! Bowls it on a length well outside off, 109.5kph, Ashutosh has to fetch it from there as he looks to heave it across. Holes out to Rashid at long-on and he did not have to move an inch. Job done from Ashutosh though. Or so we think!

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: R Ravindra
commentary: Bhuvneshwar Kumar has a first wicket in IPL 2024! He will be a relieved man. Was a back of a length ball outside off. He looks to go down the ground but the ball gets big on him. He ends up slicing it straight up and mid-on settles under it comfortably

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: RD Gaikwad
shortText: c Abdul Samad b Shahbaz Ahmed
commentary: And gets a wicket first ball. Gaikwad saw his chance to score some runs but failed in the execution. Was a gentle length ball on middle stump. The CSK captain tries to get under the ball, fails to do it and as a result does not get a decent connection. The ball finds the inside half of the blade and long-on takes a simple catch

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: AM Rahane
commentary: Taken by backward point and Unadkat ends Rahane's misery. Slower offcutter bowled at 105kph outside off. Was fuller in length as Rahane looked to go over cover. Gets it off the cue end of the bat and Markande takes a good catch behind him

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: S Dube
commentary: Soft dismissal and captain Cummins has the big fish! Slower bouncer outside off. He stays legside of the ball, deceived by the pace of the ball. He can only bunt it to backward point who takes the easiest of catches

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: RA Jadeja

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: DJ Mitchell
commentary: Straight to long-on! Fuller on the stumps, he gets under the ball but does not get the elevation. Long-on takes a simple catch

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: MS Dhoni

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: TM Head
commentary: Ravindra almost messes it up! It was coming straight to him but he fumbled and managed to keep it in in the second attempt. And Head CANNOT believe what he has done - found the fielder perfectly. Theekshana tossed it up outside leg, the offspinner, the hit-me ball. Head obliged but not in the desired manner

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Abhishek Sharma
commentary: End of the Abhishek Sharma show! The loud roar may not indicate that this is a home game for SRH. And Chahar is pumped up. Should have had a wicket in the opening over, but does so after taking a battering. Bowls it on a length outside off, Abhishek goes for a lofted shot over cover but slices it off the outer half. Jadeja runs to his right from backward point takes it reverse-cupped with a dive. Chahar exults

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: AK Markram
commentary: LBW appeal, given! Markram looks at the non-striker, who immediately asks him to go for the review. Has that turned a bit too much? Moeen tosses it up and lands it on a length outside off, Markram goes for the reverse sweep but misses because of the spin. Three reds and huge cheers in Hyderabad. Should make the list of soft dismissals for Markram, having looked at complete ease upto this point

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: Shahbaz Ahmed
commentary: Moeen and Dhoni appeal for lbw. You could almost not hear it. And next scene, they signal for DRS. Tossed up full on middle and leg, Shahbaz goes for the reverse sweep. Looks to have missed it. Did it pitch in line? Did it miss the bat? Replays taking time to load. No bat involved. And three reds again! Moeen strikes twice in two overs. Shahbaz looked unusually jittery this over

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: H Klaasen

venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Uppal, Hyderabad
name: K Nitish Kumar Reddy
F du Plessis
commentary: Chahal has his man this time, keeps the line wide and has Faf fetching. Holed out to long-on. Buttler ran across to the left, held his balance and took it low. Faf tried to heave it across. The length was there but he danced down and Chahal went wider. Faf continued trying to break free, perishes in the process. His off-day might be a big issue for the day but might be a bigger worry big-picture wise

name: GJ Maxwell
commentary: All three stumps are rattled. That's one for the fast-bowlers' posters. Maxwell made room, had feet wide apart again and tried to heave it over midwicket. Hard-length ball did him for pace and direction. Bails fly all over the place. Burger does his signature celebration

name: SD Chauhan
commentary: Taken on the second attempt by Jaiswal at cover. Chahal though, bowling slow at the death is bravery. Kept it away from the arc though, on a length and Chauhan reached out to try and cut it over the in-field. Got it off the bottom. Jaiswal's fumble was a non-issue as it popped up very close and right in front

name: YBK Jaiswal
commentary: gottim, Jaiswal goes for a duck. Takes a step out of his crease and Topley responds by digging the ball short outside off. Gets it to bounce awkwardly as Jaiswal looks to drag a pull from well outside his body, and ends up skewing a top-edge high in the air for Glenn Maxwell to get under at mid-off. Just the start RCB wanted

name: SV Samson
shortText: c Yash Dayal b Mohammed Siraj
commentary: got him, Siraj ends the partnership with a well-directed short ball. Angles it in, gets it to bounce to shoulder height, cramps Samson for room. He takes on the hook, and it almost comes off, but Dayal takes the catch at deep backward square leg with his right foot an inch short of the boundary cushion

name: R Parag
commentary: timed perfectly, and straight to the fielder. Back of a length, angling into off stump, flicked imperiously off the hip but straight into Kohli's hands at short midwicket. Catches it in front of his right shoulder with the reverse-cup

name: DC Jurel
commentary: given, and Jurel goes to the old strangle down the leg side. Length ball down the leg side, looks to flick it away, gets a nice, audible inside edge and DK does the rest

name: RG Sharma
commentary: Through his defenses and didn't DC need that! Was bowled much quicker at 102.9kph and the ball skids through after pitching. Rohit is camped on the backfoot and pokes at it. Gets beaten and the ball clatters into the off pole

name: Ishan Kishan
commentary: That is an absolute stunner! Oh, my word AXAR! Flatter length ball on off stump, Kishan hops back and absolutely belts it to Axar's left. He flings out his left hand and takes a stunner. Surely, a contender for the catch of the tournament

name: SA Yadav
commentary: A two-ball duck for Suryakumar Yadav on return. On a length on middle and leg, he looks to clear mid-on but does not get the right of timing on it. Jake Fraser-McGurk, out as a substitute, runs back and takes a good catch, reverse-cupped.

name: HH Pandya
commentary: Knee-high full toss and Hardik can only help it to deep backward square leg. He goes for 39 off 33. Was there to be hit. The ball was leg stump, but Hardik just didn't get enough bat on that. Another catch for Jake Fraser-McGurk

name: NT Tilak Varma
commentary: Straight to backward point and Mumbai are losing their way! Was a short and wide ball, there to be hit. He looks to go up and over point, but does not get on top of the bounce. Cuts it straight to Axar who is having a good day on the field. The ball was travelling.

name: PP Shaw
commentary: cleans him up with a toe-crusher! Full, fast, the late tail. It curves in furiously as Prithvi jams his bat down to keep it out, but is beaten by a few milliseconds as the leg-stump is flattened. Bumrah is chuffed. How often does he do that?

name: DA Warner
commentary: bottom hand comes off the bat handle as he reaches out to slog across the line, but the slower ball gets him! Warner holes out to mid-on as he gets absolutely no power or timing behind that stroke. Simplest of catches for Hardik.

name: Abishek Porel
commentary: heaves this full toss straight to long-on. No control or timing on that shot, hit it off the bottom. Easy as catches go.

name: RR Pant
commentary: strange little innings from Pant is over. Was looking to helicopter this over midwicket, ends up getting a leading edge to cover. Didn't look in any control today.

name: AR Patel
commentary: heaved sown to wide long-on, they'll take two. Wonder if Stubbs needed to take a single off the third ball. But anyway, what's happened here is Axar has been run out at the striker's end because of some lazy running. He was ambling for the second, under the assumption no one was in a hurry. Kishan didn't give any hint of the throw coming his way. But then suddenly gathered the throw and broke the bails to catch him a few yards short. Tardy from Axar.

name: Lalit Yadav
commentary: excellent catch from Ishan Kishan! Swirler as Lalit Yadav looks to fetch this slog from outside off only to get the top edge, Kishan called for it, ran towards where backward square leg would be and picked it nicely.

name: K Kushagra
commentary: sliced over the infield to point, as easy as catches come for Tilak. Kushagra was looking to go down the ground but the ball got away from his arc.

name: JA Richardson
commentary: the short ball has done the trick for Coetzee yet again this over. Short, angling away, beats Richardson for pace as he looks to pull in front of square, slices it straight to Rohit at point. Mumbai Indians are off the mark in IPL 2024.

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: Q de Kock
commentary: gone this time! Umesh Yadav has the early breakthrough! Back of a length delivery on leg stump, and this seems to just hold in the surface a shade. de Kock tries to repeat the dose from earlier in the over but ends up swiping across it a touch early. The ball skews up off the leading edge towards third man, where Noor runs in a few yards, settles under it and catches it in front of his face. Just the start LSG would not have wanted!

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KL Rahul
commentary: Rahul tries to go big, and perishes! This is right in the slot, just outside off, and it is there to be hit. Rahul decides to go downtown but loses his shape just a little. Gets it off the toe-end, and Tewatia, stationed at long on, settles under it, completing the catch comfortably. Rahul is not happy with himself, and he walks back having scored just 33 off 31!

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: D Padikkal
commentary: edged and gone! Umesh has two in the powerplay! Back of a length delivery in the channel. Nips away with the angle and Padikkal is enticed into wafting at it. Gets a thick outside edge and Shankar snaffles it up at wide slip, low to his left. Umesh is pumped, Padikkal utterly distraught. LSG have been rocked early!

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: MP Stoinis
commentary: two sixes and out! Nalkande gets the big fish! Back of a length on middle and off. Stoinis, fresh after two sixes, decides to make it three in the over. The ball seems to stick just a little and Stoinis loses his shape too. Goes straight up off the toe-end, and Sharath, despite circling under it nervously, snares the chance in the end!

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: N Pooran

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: A Badoni
commentary: holes out to deep mid wicket! Googly on a length on middle and off. Badoni seems to pick it and looks for the slog sweep. This has been bowled a little slower, though, meaning that Badoni has to drag it. Does not have enough behind the stroke and picks out Umesh to perfection!

venue: Bharat Ratna Shri Atal Bihari Vajpayee Ekana Cricket Stadium, Lucknow
name: KH Pandya
